ng coverage instrumentation**\\n\\nI'm trying to understand if the coverage instrumentation tracks calls in a native image instead of during Java tests. I‚Äôm thinking that maybe the test caught an `ObjenesisException` before it reached `class$`, but for `getDeclaredMethod` to work, it had to resolve `ObjectInputStream` and `Class.class` via `class$`. The JAR has synthetic fields, but our reset uses field names with `$`. If the reset fails, the test would likely error, but maybe it wouldn't. This needs some careful thought!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating app class access**\\n\\nI'm considering whether Class.forName is accessible if the app class is reachable. It looks like the existing GCJ passes, so I might need to add a method. I should also read the current file before making any edits and commit those changes. Since previous commits exist, I‚Äôll need to create a new commit, but I won't run tests at this stage. Let's see how this goes!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Zi3M4UIFZ0jiZFuaaYgeEDFS|fc_0e345a3b16969c960169ef7cbca80881958170d3fc6be10015", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.objenesis/objenesis/1.2/src/test/java/org_objenesis/objenesis/Sun13InstantiatorBaseTest.java"}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_YDcZmAKbYUl8oF5BEx9aCBax|fc_0e345a3b16969c960169ef7cbca8188195950643afc126d6a7", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git status --short --untracked-files=all && git log -3 --oneline", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 7119, "output": 1030, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27093, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777302700246, "responseId": "resp_0e345a3b16969c960169ef7cad9e008195a7317b0aa37042ad"}}
